  "chapter": {
    "number": 16,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job Decries His Comforters"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Job answered:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "â€œI have heard many things like these;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "miserable comforters are you all.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is there no end to your long-winded speeches?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "What provokes you to continue testifying?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I could also speak like you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if you were in my place;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I could heap up words against you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and shake my head at you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But I would encourage you with my mouth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the consolation of my lips would bring relief.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even if I speak, my pain is not relieved,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and if I hold back, how will it go away?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely He has now exhausted me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have devastated all my family.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have bound me, and it has become a witness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my frailty rises up and testifies against me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His anger has torn me and opposed me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He gnashes His teeth at me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "My adversary pierces me with His eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They open their mouths against me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and strike my cheeks with contempt;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they join together against me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "God has delivered me to unjust men;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has thrown me to the clutches of the wicked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I was at ease, but He shattered me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He seized me by the neck and crushed me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has set me up as His target;",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His archers surround me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He pierces my kidneys without mercy",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and spills my gall on the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He breaks me with wound upon wound;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He rushes me like a mighty warrior.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have sewn sackcloth over my skin;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have buried my horn in the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My face is red with weeping,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and deep shadows ring my eyes;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "yet my hands are free of violence",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my prayer is pure.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O earth, do not cover my blood;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may my cry for help never be laid to rest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even now my witness is in heaven,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my advocate is on high.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My friends are my scoffers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as my eyes pour out tears to God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Oh, that a man might plead with God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as he pleads with his neighbor!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For when only a few years are past",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will go the way of no return.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
